6d2b64f5-40d2-447d-9934-f46a80970b36 Grate the zest and squeeze out the juice of the lime. Add these to the avocado mixture with the chili, salt, and pepper. Add the Parmesan, stir well, and place the mixture in the refrigerator for 10 minutes.

236a9028-d287-44ec-9da1-84b37213dc4c Preheat the oven to 300 F. Line a baking sheet with a silicone mat or line with parchment paper and spray with nonstick spray.
236a9028-d287-44ec-9da1-84b37213dc4c Separate the eggs, placing the whites in one mixing bowl and the yolks in another mixing bowl.
236a9028-d287-44ec-9da1-84b37213dc4c Add the cream of tartar to the egg whites. Beat the whites with a hand mixer until stiff peaks form, or about 2 to 3 minutes. When you dip a beater from the mixer into the eggs and pull it out, a peak should form and stay standing up. Don't over-beat the eggs or they will become crumbly.
236a9028-d287-44ec-9da1-84b37213dc4c Add the cream cheese and salt to the bowl with the egg yolks. Beat until smooth.
236a9028-d287-44ec-9da1-84b37213dc4c Carefully add about 1/3 of the egg whites to the yolks mixture. Carefully fold the two mixtures together, careful not to deflate the egg whites. Repeat two more times with the remaining egg whites, folding in just until mixed.
236a9028-d287-44ec-9da1-84b37213dc4c Scoop out into 6 to 8 separate disks (depending on what size you want) onto the prepared baking sheet, leaving them at least 2 to 3 inches apart.
236a9028-d287-44ec-9da1-84b37213dc4c Bake 25 to 35 minutes depending on the size of your clouds, or until golden brown. Start checking the breads at the 25 minute mark since they can overcook easily.
236a9028-d287-44ec-9da1-84b37213dc4c Let cool for a few minutes on the baking sheet before placing on a cooling rack. Store leftover cloud breads in an airtight container for up to 3 days or freeze.

70c72ee8-1f06-45bb-a651-cf5b33294f5a Cook the pancakes for about a minute and then flip the pancakes over. Turn the heat down if you need to so that they do not burn. Cook time may vary depending on your stove top.
70c72ee8-1f06-45bb-a651-cf5b33294f5a Serve the pancakes with extra butter and dig in!
2f59da28-ca14-4d62-a117-98d334db5e08 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 400 F.
2f59da28-ca14-4d62-a117-98d334db5e08 Place the cauliflower florets into your food processor and pulse until the cauliflower is the size of rice. You can do this in batches to cut down on dealing with large pieces.
2f59da28-ca14-4d62-a117-98d334db5e08 Add the shredded cheese, egg, egg white, tapioca, garlic powder, salt, and pepper to the bowl of the food processor and pulse until combined.
2f59da28-ca14-4d62-a117-98d334db5e08 Scoop 1/4 cup of the cauliflower mixture onto a parchment-lined baking sheet.
2f59da28-ca14-4d62-a117-98d334db5e08 Place another piece of parchment paper on top of the cauliflower scoops and press down with another baking sheet of the same size until you have created a thin circle (about a 1/4 inch thick).
2f59da28-ca14-4d62-a117-98d334db5e08 Slowly remove the parchment paper. If it sticks to the parchment, just reshape it a little with your hands.
2f59da28-ca14-4d62-a117-98d334db5e08 Place the baking sheet in the preheated oven and bake for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned and firm.
2f59da28-ca14-4d62-a117-98d334db5e08 Remove the tortillas from the oven, allow them to cool slightly and serve them with your favorite taco fillings.
1ed685aa-b72c-4681-a45d-1e4579cab1de Gather the ingredients.
1ed685aa-b72c-4681-a45d-1e4579cab1de Add the olive oil to a sauté pan and heat on medium-high heat. Add the minced onion and sauté until translucent and soft.
1ed685aa-b72c-4681-a45d-1e4579cab1de Add the broth to the pan and heat for about five minutes. Add the contents to a blender and puree until completely smooth.
1ed685aa-b72c-4681-a45d-1e4579cab1de Temper the egg yolks with the hot broth by adding a little bit of the hot broth to the egg yolks while whisking vigorously. Keep adding the broth until it is incorporated into the eggs.
1ed685aa-b72c-4681-a45d-1e4579cab1de Soften the gelatin with the cold water. Stir until the gelatin dissolves.
1ed685aa-b72c-4681-a45d-1e4579cab1de Add the gravy back to the blender along with the gelatin and pepper. Blend until completely smooth. Then blend for another 2 minutes or until the gravy is slightly thickened. Blend in the butter if you wish.
1ed685aa-b72c-4681-a45d-1e4579cab1de Serve the gravy over your favorite turkey or mashed cauliflower.
92472a05-57d0-4837-8d72-5611ab6e9b07 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 375 F.
92472a05-57d0-4837-8d72-5611ab6e9b07 In a small mixing bowl, whisk cream cheese with the 2 tablespoons of sweetener and set aside.
92472a05-57d0-4837-8d72-5611ab6e9b07 Combine the almond flour, 3/4 cup of the sweetener, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice, and salt in a large mixing bowl.
92472a05-57d0-4837-8d72-5611ab6e9b07 Add pumpkin puree, yogurt, eggs, and oil, and whisk until a thick batter is formed.
92472a05-57d0-4837-8d72-5611ab6e9b07 Divide batter between 12 greased and/or lined muffin tin cups, then place a dollop of cream cheese in each. Stir cream cheese mix with a toothpick to create a swirl in each muffin.
92472a05-57d0-4837-8d72-5611ab6e9b07 Bake for 22 minutes, until set and golden.
92472a05-57d0-4837-8d72-5611ab6e9b07 Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from the pan and serving.
8d87e8b3-f96d-4b76-8d16-b0d08f06e5af Gather the ingredients. Preheat your oven to 350 F.
8d87e8b3-f96d-4b76-8d16-b0d08f06e5af In a mixing bowl, stir together all dry ingredients (almond flour to pumpkin pie spice) with a fork.
8d87e8b3-f96d-4b76-8d16-b0d08f06e5af Add all remaining ingredients and stir with a fork until free of lumps.
8d87e8b3-f96d-4b76-8d16-b0d08f06e5af Pour batter into a greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and place in the oven.
8d87e8b3-f96d-4b76-8d16-b0d08f06e5af Let cool before removing from the pan, then slice and enjoy.
0406c60d-e313-485c-930e-ed7e90a1aaa3 Gather the ingredients.
0406c60d-e313-485c-930e-ed7e90a1aaa3 Preheat the oven to 250 F. Add the cubed cornbread to a parchment-lined baking sheet. Make sure the pieces are spread around and arent too cramped. Place the pan in the oven and bake for about an hour or until they are golden brown, crunchy, and dried out.
0406c60d-e313-485c-930e-ed7e90a1aaa3 Add the butter to a sauté pan over medium heat and allow it to melt. Then add the onion and celery. Sauté until the vegetables are soft and translucent.
0406c60d-e313-485c-930e-ed7e90a1aaa3 Whisk together the broth, eggs, poultry seasoning, salt, pepper, and thyme in a measuring cup or a bowl.
0406c60d-e313-485c-930e-ed7e90a1aaa3 Toss together the toasted bread cubes, sautéed vegetables, and the chopped parsley and sage in a casserole dish.
0406c60d-e313-485c-930e-ed7e90a1aaa3 Pour the liquid mixture over the top of the casserole. It should cover most of the bread cubes. Cover the pan and bake for about 40 minutes or until all of the liquid has been absorbed. Remove the foil and put the casserole back in the oven for about 10 minutes, until the top is crispy and browned.
0406c60d-e313-485c-930e-ed7e90a1aaa3 Serve with more chopped fresh parsley. Enjoy!
61918bf1-01bc-4206-b0dd-c268fc165959 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
61918bf1-01bc-4206-b0dd-c268fc165959 Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl and whisk until all lumps have disappeared.
61918bf1-01bc-4206-b0dd-c268fc165959 Pour mixture into a greased and/or parchment lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
61918bf1-01bc-4206-b0dd-c268fc165959 Bake in preheated oven until set, about 55 minutes. Let cool completely before removing from the pan.
0c8649b6-be5c-460a-a062-3cb6f03474d7 Gather the ingredients and make sure you have enough flat, empty space in your freezer to fit your popsicle mold tray.
0c8649b6-be5c-460a-a062-3cb6f03474d7 Reserve 3/4 cup of the strawberries. Add the cream cheese, heavy cream, allulose, and the remaining 1 cup of the strawberries to a blender. Blend the mixture until smooth, then add the reserved strawberries. Pour mixture directly from blender pitcher into a 10-popsicle tray, filling each. Place the lid on the tray and insert popsicle sticks into the openings, leaving about 2 inches of stick out. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
0c8649b6-be5c-460a-a062-3cb6f03474d7 To unmold, take tray out of the freezer and remove the lid. If popsicles are stuck to the tray, as they likely will be, run the plastic outside of the tray under warm water for 10 seconds, then take popsicles out of the molds. Serve right away and enjoy!
cde6ff7d-b49c-4431-b22d-3afae7e2d1f4 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 425 F.
cde6ff7d-b49c-4431-b22d-3afae7e2d1f4 Peel the outer skin of the jicama. Cut into fry-like pieces. They should be thick enough to turn easily with tongs, but thin enough that they will crisp up in the oven.
cde6ff7d-b49c-4431-b22d-3afae7e2d1f4 Place the jicama pieces in a single layer on a large baking sheet. Do not overcrowd or overlap or the pieces will not crisp well. Depending on the size of your jicama or the baking sheet, two baking sheets might be necessary to avoid overcrowding. Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat.
cde6ff7d-b49c-4431-b22d-3afae7e2d1f4 In a small bowl, combine the chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, kosher salt, and ground cumin. Sprinkle the seasoning mix over the jicama and toss to coat. Roast in the oven for 15 minutes, then flip all of the fries to crisp the other side, about 10 to 15 minutes more. The jicama fries should be slightly browned and crispy.
cde6ff7d-b49c-4431-b22d-3afae7e2d1f4 Before serving, squeeze the fries with fresh lime juice and sprinkle with chopped fresh cilantro. Season with additional salt and pepper to taste.
cde6ff7d-b49c-4431-b22d-3afae7e2d1f4 Enjoy!
735aa4be-b885-4590-aed5-301e7ec6a1cb Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F. Prepare a baking sheet by covering with parchment paper.
735aa4be-b885-4590-aed5-301e7ec6a1cb In a medium bowl, combine blanched almond flour, keto sugar, melted coconut oil, lemon juice, lemon zest, and sea salt.
735aa4be-b885-4590-aed5-301e7ec6a1cb Mix well, breaking up any lumps in the flour and sugar. The dough will be slightly crumbly but will press together in your hand.
735aa4be-b885-4590-aed5-301e7ec6a1cb Roll into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on the prepared baking sheet.
735aa4be-b885-4590-aed5-301e7ec6a1cb Place one whole almond in the center of each ball and press down to flatten slightly.
735aa4be-b885-4590-aed5-301e7ec6a1cb Cool the cookies on the baking sheet for 10 minutes. Transfer to a wire rack and cool completely.
735aa4be-b885-4590-aed5-301e7ec6a1cb Because of the high fat content in the almond flour and coconut oil, it is best to store these cookies in an airtight container in the refrigerator. They will keep in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks or can be frozen for up to 6 months.
c9fc4dc3-7d7e-41a6-aecd-c59900d5938d Gather the ingredients.
c9fc4dc3-7d7e-41a6-aecd-c59900d5938d Trim all of the fat off of the meat. Fat does not dehydrate well, will create an unpleasant texture if left on the meat, and can cause faster decay.
c9fc4dc3-7d7e-41a6-aecd-c59900d5938d With a very sharp knife, slice the beef with or against the grain depending on your preferred texture. Cut it thinly, at least 1/4-inch thick, if not thinner. Freezing the meet for one hour prior to slicing will make this process much easier.
c9fc4dc3-7d7e-41a6-aecd-c59900d5938d Mix the marinade ingredients in a non-reactive bowl.
c9fc4dc3-7d7e-41a6-aecd-c59900d5938d Place the slices of meat in the bowl. Mix well, cover with plastic wrap, and marinate the meat for 10 hours in the fridge. Toss the meat around once or twice during the process.
c9fc4dc3-7d7e-41a6-aecd-c59900d5938d Once the marinating time is over, place the meat in a colander and drain off the liquid.
c9fc4dc3-7d7e-41a6-aecd-c59900d5938d Mix all of the dry rub ingredients in a medium-sized bowl.
c9fc4dc3-7d7e-41a6-aecd-c59900d5938d Once the meat is drained, dip both sides of each slice of meat into the dry rub.
c9fc4dc3-7d7e-41a6-aecd-c59900d5938d Follow the instructions for oven or dehydrator method, depending on which appliance you will be using.
1c70ce29-6789-4680-8e34-6a57d678f2f5 Gather the ingredients.
1c70ce29-6789-4680-8e34-6a57d678f2f5 Set a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the oil or butter. Once hot, add the riced cauliflower. Cook, stirring frequently, until the cauliflower is tender, but still has a little bite, about 5 to 7 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
1c70ce29-6789-4680-8e34-6a57d678f2f5 Remove from heat, add the lime juice and chopped cilantro, and toss to combine. Serve immediately.
a7291827-8b1b-41c1-a883-848e35a5b67b Gather the ingredients. Before you start, chill your stand mixer bowl in the freezer for 15 minutes.
a7291827-8b1b-41c1-a883-848e35a5b67b Carefully open the can by a few inches and slowly drain any liquid into a bowl. Do not shake or force the liquid out, let gravity do its work. Keep the liquid for soups, curries, or add to your morning smoothie.
a7291827-8b1b-41c1-a883-848e35a5b67b Fully open the can. Use a spoon to scoop out the thick cream into the chilled bowl of a stand mixer, avoiding adding any of the remaining liquid. Add agave and vanilla extract if using. Place the bowl on your mixer.
a7291827-8b1b-41c1-a883-848e35a5b67b Using the whisk attachment, start to whisk the coconut milk on a low speed, gradually increasing the speed to high. Let the mixer run for between 8 to 10 minutes. Once it is thickened and light and airy, stop the mixer. Unlike dairy cream, coconut whipped cream will not curdle, but over-whipping will flatten the cream.
a7291827-8b1b-41c1-a883-848e35a5b67b Serve the coconut cream immediately on your favorite desserts, cakes, or sundaes.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Gather the ingredients. Heat the oven to 350 F.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Put the thawed riced cauliflower on a few doubled sheets of paper towel or a kitchen towel and squeeze out any excess moisture. Set aside.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes. Add the ground beef and bell pepper and continue to cook until the meat is browned.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Add the taco seasoning and stir until well blended.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Layer about half of the beef mixture in a 2-quart baking dish or casserole; top with about 1/2 cup of shredded cheese.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Top the ground beef and cheese with the riced cauliflower and another 1/2 cup of shredded cheese.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Top with the remaining beef and another 1/2 cup of shredded cheese.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Spoon the salsa evenly over the second ground beef and cheese layers.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Heat the cream in a saucepan over medium heat. Add 1 cup of shredded cheese and cook, stirring, until the cheese is melted, about two minutes.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Pour the cream and cheese sauce mixture over the salsa layer. Top with the remaining 1/2 cup of shredded cheese.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Bake the casserole for 30 to 40 minutes, or until hot and bubbly. Garnish with chopped cilantro, if desired.
4b1bdbad-ed0a-4b5f-8468-c92404fca9ee Serve the casserole with toppings, such as extra salsa, chopped green onions, avocado slices, guacamole, diced tomatoes, sliced olives, jalapeño pepper rings, or sour cream.
d3cef745-593e-46da-99ac-fe9d2bb0f28e Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease the doughnut pans and set aside.
d3cef745-593e-46da-99ac-fe9d2bb0f28e In a large bowl, stir together the blanched almond flour, sugar substitute, baking powder, ground cinnamon, and salt.
d3cef745-593e-46da-99ac-fe9d2bb0f28e In a small bowl, whisk together the melted butter, unsweetened almond milk, eggs, and vanilla extract.
d3cef745-593e-46da-99ac-fe9d2bb0f28e Add the egg mixture to the almond flour mixture and stir to combine.
d3cef745-593e-46da-99ac-fe9d2bb0f28e Spoon the batter into the prepared doughnut pans, filling them 3/4 of the way to the top. Bake for 25 to 28 minutes, or until a dark golden-brown color.
d3cef745-593e-46da-99ac-fe9d2bb0f28e Remove the doughnuts from the pan and cool on a wire rack.
d3cef745-593e-46da-99ac-fe9d2bb0f28e In a small bowl, combine the 1/2 cup of keto-friendly sugar substitute with the cinnamon. Working one at a time, brush both sides of the doughnut with the 3 tablespoons of melted butter, then press the doughnut in the sweetener and cinnamon mixture to coat. Repeat with the remaining doughnuts.
d3cef745-593e-46da-99ac-fe9d2bb0f28e Enjoy!
302fab6f-5173-4dc0-9096-5acb37caa9e3 Gather the ingredients.
302fab6f-5173-4dc0-9096-5acb37caa9e3 Whisk the egg until it is completely blended. Whisk in 1/2 cup of the cheese.
302fab6f-5173-4dc0-9096-5acb37caa9e3 Heat a mini waffle iron on high heat. Sprinkle some of the leftover cheese on the bottom of the iron.
302fab6f-5173-4dc0-9096-5acb37caa9e3 Pour half of the batter into the waffle iron and then top with another sprinkle of cheese if you wish.
302fab6f-5173-4dc0-9096-5acb37caa9e3 Cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
302fab6f-5173-4dc0-9096-5acb37caa9e3 Remove and place on a plate or cooling rack to cool while you prepare the second half of the batter. The waffle will continue to crisp as it cools.
302fab6f-5173-4dc0-9096-5acb37caa9e3 Serve with butter and keto-friendly syrup for a sweet breakfast. Or use it as bread on your favorite sandwich.
6997cf33-cc9c-41be-ac6e-7414c428e8c5 Gather the ingredients. Heat the oven to 250 F and remove the pork chops from the refrigerator.
6997cf33-cc9c-41be-ac6e-7414c428e8c5 Sprinkle salt and pepper evenly onto a chopping board. Press each pork chop into the seasoning, flip them over, and press again. Add a little more salt and pepper if more is needed on the other side.
6997cf33-cc9c-41be-ac6e-7414c428e8c5 Heat a ridged grill pan over medium heat and add the olive oil and the butter. Once the butter is foaming, add the two pork chops and cook on one side for 7 minutes. Flip the chops over and cook a further 7 minutes. The fat on the chops should be nicely browned with good grill marks on the meat. When pressed in the center with a finger, the chops should be firm but not hard.
6997cf33-cc9c-41be-ac6e-7414c428e8c5 Remove the chops from the pan and keep the pan to one side, unwashed. Place the chops into an ovenproof dish, cover with foil, and put into the warm oven to rest.
6997cf33-cc9c-41be-ac6e-7414c428e8c5 Break the broccoli florets and break into small pieces. Put the pan back over medium heat, add the florets, and cook them for 3 minutes, shaking the pan from time to time. The florets should start to color. Remove from the pan and keep to one side.
6997cf33-cc9c-41be-ac6e-7414c428e8c5 Raise the heat under the pan slightly. Once hot, add the white wine to deglaze the pan and stir to scrape up any bits from cooking. Let the wine bubble to reduce to approximately one tablespoon.
6997cf33-cc9c-41be-ac6e-7414c428e8c5 Lower the heat back to medium and add the chicken stock. Let it simmer until reduced by half. Stir the cream into the sauce and add the fennel fronds. Cook for a few minutes more. Add the broccoli to the sauce and stir in the Parmesan cheese.
6997cf33-cc9c-41be-ac6e-7414c428e8c5 Remove the foil from the pork chops, pour the sauce and veggies over, and serve.
8ae0376f-a70c-4cc7-90f4-de2d67679c6a Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 350 F.
8ae0376f-a70c-4cc7-90f4-de2d67679c6a In a large bowl, combine the almond flour with the salt.
8ae0376f-a70c-4cc7-90f4-de2d67679c6a Add the melted coconut oil and egg. Stir to combine.
8ae0376f-a70c-4cc7-90f4-de2d67679c6a Spoon the pie crust dough into a 9-inch pie pan.
8ae0376f-a70c-4cc7-90f4-de2d67679c6a Evenly press the pie crust into the bottom and up the sides of the pan.
8ae0376f-a70c-4cc7-90f4-de2d67679c6a Using a fork, press indentations into the top edge of the pie crust for decoration.
8ae0376f-a70c-4cc7-90f4-de2d67679c6a Bake in the preheated oven for 8 to 12 minutes, or until lightly golden brown.
8ae0376f-a70c-4cc7-90f4-de2d67679c6a Cool completely before filling with any pie filling of your choice or as a replacement gluten-free crust in any no-bake pie recipe.
ca2e3247-2891-4a9f-bb16-708b4b2c76be Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 425 F.
ca2e3247-2891-4a9f-bb16-708b4b2c76be Coat a half sheet pan with the olive oil. Place it in the preheated oven for 10 minutes.
ca2e3247-2891-4a9f-bb16-708b4b2c76be Meanwhile, crack the eggs into a quart-sized pitcher, liquid measuring cup, or anything with a wide spout that can accommodate all the eggs.
ca2e3247-2891-4a9f-bb16-708b4b2c76be Gently, yet expeditiously, pour the eggs onto the hot sheet pan, and return it to the oven. For sunnies, bake until the white is just set and the yolks are still liquid, about 5 minutes. Remove, season with salt and pepper, divide, and serve.
83251cc7-41b3-4d28-8143-382f2c778454 Gather the ingredients.
83251cc7-41b3-4d28-8143-382f2c778454 Trim the cauliflower. Cut into florets and roughly chop the stem. Peel and large dice the onion and add both to the bowl of a food processor.
83251cc7-41b3-4d28-8143-382f2c778454 Pulse a few times until diced. Add salt and pulse a couple more times until minced. Let sit for 10 minutes.
83251cc7-41b3-4d28-8143-382f2c778454 Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 400 F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
83251cc7-41b3-4d28-8143-382f2c778454 Dump the cauliflower and onion onto a clean kitchen towel or a piece of cheesecloth. Fold up the towel around the mixture and squeeze out the excess moisture. Squeeze until liquid doesn't freely drip from the towel when pressure is applied.
83251cc7-41b3-4d28-8143-382f2c778454 Add the drained cauliflower and onion to a large bowl. Add the cheese, egg, cornstarch, garlic powder, pepper, and 2 tablespoons of chives (if using). Mix well.
83251cc7-41b3-4d28-8143-382f2c778454 Divide the mixture up into six equal piles evenly spaced on the prepared baking sheet. Press the mixture together and form into six patties 1/3 to 1/2-inch thick. Brush the tops gently with the oil and sprinkle with salt.
83251cc7-41b3-4d28-8143-382f2c778454 Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until browned on top. Let cool on the pan for 5 minutes before serving.
3f0b721b-1e16-4b05-af2c-4b0a9bb83504 Gather ingredient, as well as two microwave safe plates and microwave safe paper towels.
3f0b721b-1e16-4b05-af2c-4b0a9bb83504 Line a microwave-safe plate with microwave-safe paper towels.
3f0b721b-1e16-4b05-af2c-4b0a9bb83504 Arrange six bacon slices side-by-side on the towels. Make sure the bacon doesn't overlap or the slices won't cook evenly.
3f0b721b-1e16-4b05-af2c-4b0a9bb83504 Cover the bacon with another microwave-safe paper towel to prevent splattering.
3f0b721b-1e16-4b05-af2c-4b0a9bb83504 Microwave the bacon for 3 minutes on high power and rotate the plate so the bacon cooks evenly. Cook for another minute.
3f0b721b-1e16-4b05-af2c-4b0a9bb83504 Remove the bacon from the plate and let it rest on a fresh paper towel for 2 to 3 minutes to drain off the excess fat.
3f0b721b-1e16-4b05-af2c-4b0a9bb83504 Serve bacon immediately.
15345ae5-6561-4305-b982-2f6a86f26e4c Gather the ingredients.
15345ae5-6561-4305-b982-2f6a86f26e4c Add the olive oil to a small saucepan and heat on medium-high heat. Add the shallots and salt and saute until softened and translucent, about 4 minutes. Then add in the minced garlic and saute for 1 minute on medium-low heat.
15345ae5-6561-4305-b982-2f6a86f26e4c Add the tomato paste, apple cider vinegar, erythritol, Worcestershire, liquid smoke, chili powder, smoked paprika, mustard, cumin, and water to the saucepan. Whisk and heat on medium-low heat until the ingredients have combined. Lower the heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring frequently until thickened and is slightly darker in color.
15345ae5-6561-4305-b982-2f6a86f26e4c Allow the sauce to cool slightly and then place it in a blender and blend until completely smooth. Taste and add more salt if needed.
15345ae5-6561-4305-b982-2f6a86f26e4c Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for 1 week. Or can the sauce using safe canning techniques and store in the pantry for 6 months. Serve on top of your favorite grilled meats.
3e535812-9ebb-441a-b1e6-f91b66e753a4 Gather the ingredients.
3e535812-9ebb-441a-b1e6-f91b66e753a4 Add the almonds to the bowl of a food processor. Pulse about 10 times, until some of the almonds are pulverized into powder and some are still chunky. Don't process too much or you'll make almond butter.
3e535812-9ebb-441a-b1e6-f91b66e753a4 Add the almond or nut butter, unsalted butter, confectioners' erythritol, vanilla, and salt (if using). Process for one minute, stopping halfway through to scrape down the sides.
3e535812-9ebb-441a-b1e6-f91b66e753a4 Chill the mixture in the refrigerator for 30 minutes. Use a cookie scoop to scoop the mixture into even portions and place on a parchment-lined baking sheet. If the mixture gets to warm, pop it back in the fridge for a few minutes.
3e535812-9ebb-441a-b1e6-f91b66e753a4 Melt the chocolate in the microwave, heating for 30-second intervals and stirring, or melt over a double boiler. Drizzle each of the balls with chocolate.
3e535812-9ebb-441a-b1e6-f91b66e753a4 Place the baking sheet in the freezer for 15 minutes to firm up. Store the balls in an airtight container in the fridge for up to a week.
d4eecbf3-8003-4273-ac60-ef7d76742e5e Gather the ingredients.
d4eecbf3-8003-4273-ac60-ef7d76742e5e Preheat oven to 450 F with racks in upper and lower thirds. Lightly grease a rimmed baking sheet or large oven-proof oval casserole. Leaving core and stem intact, cut the cauliflower crosswise (through the core) into 1-inch thick planks. Place in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet and season with salt and pepper. Roast on bottom rack until cauliflower is browned underneath and tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
d4eecbf3-8003-4273-ac60-ef7d76742e5e Meanwhile, use kitchen scissors to finely chop tomatoes in the can. Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a small pot over medium-high. Add garlic and cook until lightly golden and fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add tomatoes and season to taste with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium-low and cook at a vigorous simmer until sauce is slightly reduced, 7 to 8 minutes.
d4eecbf3-8003-4273-ac60-ef7d76742e5e Stir in the basil. Remove from heat and set aside.
d4eecbf3-8003-4273-ac60-ef7d76742e5e Switch oven to broil. Flip the cauliflower so the browned side is facing up. Spoon half of the sauce on top. Sprinkle mozzarella and half of the Parmesan cheese over. Broil on top rack until cheese is melted and browned in spots, 2 to 3 minutes (watch closely as broilers vary).
d4eecbf3-8003-4273-ac60-ef7d76742e5e Serve cauliflower Parmesan immediately with remaining sauce and Parmesan cheese on the side.
d892cca7-2688-4761-bcf8-6e229614163f Gather the ingredients.
d892cca7-2688-4761-bcf8-6e229614163f Add the prepared espresso to a small saucepan. The espresso can be prepared hours ahead of time or fresh. Whisk in the pumpkin puree, heavy cream, whole milk, pumpkin spice, and erythritol. Heat until steaming, then remove from the stove.
d892cca7-2688-4761-bcf8-6e229614163f Froth the contents with a hand-held frother. You can also whisk vigorously. Just be careful not to splash yourself as you are stirring.
d892cca7-2688-4761-bcf8-6e229614163f Top with prepared whipped cream and a little cinnamon or pumpkin pie spice and serve immediately.
cb9759f0-b842-47b8-b010-3d7b428959bc Gather the ingredients.
cb9759f0-b842-47b8-b010-3d7b428959bc Preheat the oven to 350 F. Combine the ground beef, sausage, and pork rinds in a large bowl. Mix until the ingredients are evenly distributed, but make sure not to over mix or else the meat will be tough.
cb9759f0-b842-47b8-b010-3d7b428959bc Whisk together the egg, milk, salt, pepper, parsley, Italian seasoning, and Parmesan cheese.
cb9759f0-b842-47b8-b010-3d7b428959bc Pour the egg mixture over the meat mixture. Add in the onion and garlic. Combine until all of the ingredients are evenly distributed.
cb9759f0-b842-47b8-b010-3d7b428959bc Form the meat mixture into a loaf shape.
cb9759f0-b842-47b8-b010-3d7b428959bc Wrap the meatloaf with the strips of bacon.
cb9759f0-b842-47b8-b010-3d7b428959bc Carefully pick up the meatloaf and place it on a cooling rack over an aluminum foil-wrapped baking sheet. Pour the tomato sauce over the top of the meatloaf.
cb9759f0-b842-47b8-b010-3d7b428959bc Bake in the preheated oven uncovered for one hour or until the top is caramelized and the internal temperature is 165 F. You can increase the temperature to 375 F for the last 5 minutes to further caramelize the top and crisp up the bacon.
cb9759f0-b842-47b8-b010-3d7b428959bc Remove from the oven and allow to cool slightly. Slice and serve immediately with your favorite keto sides, like mashed cauliflower and Brussels sprouts.
bc099172-caab-4f63-9eac-018d064bc512 Gather the ingredients.
bc099172-caab-4f63-9eac-018d064bc512 Preheat the oven to 400 F. Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
bc099172-caab-4f63-9eac-018d064bc512 Toss the cauliflower with the olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Spread out on a baking sheet and roast for about 10 minutes or until crisp-tender. Reduce the oven temperature to 375 F.
bc099172-caab-4f63-9eac-018d064bc512 Add the milk, cream cheese, mustard, turmeric, and garlic powder to a medium saucepan and heat over medium-low heat. Season with salt and pepper. Whisk until the cheese sauce is warmed through and creamy. Remove from the heat and stir in the cheddar cheese.
bc099172-caab-4f63-9eac-018d064bc512 In a large bowl, combine the cauliflower and cheese sauce and mix. Taste for seasoning. Pour into the prepared baking dish and top with Parmesan cheese.
bc099172-caab-4f63-9eac-018d064bc512 Bake for about 20 minutes or until bubbly, warmed all the way through and browning on top. If you'd like your mac and cheese browner on top, place under the broiler for 1 or 2 minutes.
bc099172-caab-4f63-9eac-018d064bc512 Serve warm.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 400 F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 In a microwave-safe bowl, melt the mozzarella cheese and cream cheese in 30-second increments until completely melted.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 Whisk together 2 of the eggs, almond flour, baking powder, and salt.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 Add the almond flour mixture to the melted cheese and mix until it forms a soft dough. Use a hand mixer to achieve the right consistency. The dough should feel soft and only slightly tacky.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 Divide the dough into 30 small balls.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 Shape each ball into a 3- to 4-inch rope.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 Wrap the rope around each hot dog 2 to 3 times. Place them on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Make sure they have a good amount of space between each of them. They will puff a bit when they cook.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 Add a teaspoon of water to the final egg and whisk until combined. Brush the egg mixture over the top of each hot dog.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 Bake in the preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. The dough should also look firm to the touch.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 Whisk together the melted butter and garlic powder in a small bowl. Brush the top of each dog with the garlic butter. Sprinkle the top of each dog with the everything bagel seasoning.
029e2525-c89b-4083-a6e1-c652d04e3760 Serve immediately with your favorite dips.
e6f3da08-d20f-4c69-91f6-76a0f583e357 Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 350 F. Prepare a baking sheet by covering with parchment paper.
e6f3da08-d20f-4c69-91f6-76a0f583e357 In a large bowl, combine the natural peanut butter, unsweetened coconut, xylitol, eggs, vanilla extract, and sea salt.
e6f3da08-d20f-4c69-91f6-76a0f583e357 Stir until completely smooth. Refrigerate at least 15 minutes to firm slightly.
e6f3da08-d20f-4c69-91f6-76a0f583e357 When the dough is firm enough to handle, roll into 1-inch balls and place 1 inch apart on prepared baking sheets.
e6f3da08-d20f-4c69-91f6-76a0f583e357 Using a fork, press the top of each cookie in a crisscross pattern. If the fork sticks to the cookies when pressing, dip the fork in additional xylitol as necessary.
e6f3da08-d20f-4c69-91f6-76a0f583e357 Bake in the preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until the cookies are set.
e6f3da08-d20f-4c69-91f6-76a0f583e357 Remove to a wire rack to cool completely.
e6f3da08-d20f-4c69-91f6-76a0f583e357 Store in an airtight container.
e6f3da08-d20f-4c69-91f6-76a0f583e357 Enjoy!
de535fd5-be19-4ce8-9307-dae86cd57290 Gather the ingredients. Line two large baking sheets with parchment paper and preheat the oven to 400 F.
de535fd5-be19-4ce8-9307-dae86cd57290 Add the yeast, sugar, and warm water to a small bowl and mix. Set aside to let the yeast proof for about 5 minutes. Make sure you use warm water and not hot water to avoid killing the yeast.
de535fd5-be19-4ce8-9307-dae86cd57290 Add the mozzarella and cream cheese to a microwave-safe bowl. Cook for 30-second intervals, stirring each time, until the cheeses are fully melted. Alternatively, place the cheeses in a heat-proof bowl and place over simmering water. Stir until the cheeses are melted.
de535fd5-be19-4ce8-9307-dae86cd57290 Add the almond flour, baking powder, and xanthan gum to a food processor with a dough blade or a stand mixer with the dough attachment. Mix to combine. Add the eggs and 1 tablespoon of melted butter and pulse or mix until well combined.
de535fd5-be19-4ce8-9307-dae86cd57290 Add the yeast mixture and pulse or mix until combined. Add the cheese and process or mix until a cohesive dough forms, or about 5 minutes. Stop halfway through and scrape down the sides with a rubber spatula. Turn out of the bowl and form into a flat ball. Cut into 12 wedges.
de535fd5-be19-4ce8-9307-dae86cd57290 Roll each wedge, one at a time, into a rope about 16 inches long. Form into a pretzel shape and press lightly where the dough intersects. Move to the prepared cookie sheet. Repeat with the remaining dough, placing six pretzels on each pan. Brush with the remaining butter and sprinkle with salt.
de535fd5-be19-4ce8-9307-dae86cd57290 Bake for about 12 minutes, or until puffed, browned, and cooked through. Rotate the pans halfway through baking for the best results. Let cool for just a couple of minutes before serving warm.
92b1be12-5a73-4e14-822c-00cd9c9494d4 Gather the ingredients.
92b1be12-5a73-4e14-822c-00cd9c9494d4 Preheat oven broiler with an oven rack 6 inches from the heat source. Line a rimmed baking sheet with foil, then add tofu. Toss tofu with 1 tablespoon oil. Broil on top rack, flipping once, until golden and crisp, 8 to 10 minutes (watch carefully as broilers vary).
92b1be12-5a73-4e14-822c-00cd9c9494d4 In a medium bowl, combine the fish sauce, tamarind, sugar, cilantro stems, and 2 tablespoons water; whisk to blend then set aside to let sugar and tamarind dissolve.
92b1be12-5a73-4e14-822c-00cd9c9494d4 In a small bowl, beat eggs. Heat 1 tablespoon in a medium skillet over medium-high. Add eggs, and cook, stirring, until cooked through, about 1 minute; transfer to a bowl. Rinse and dry skillet.
92b1be12-5a73-4e14-822c-00cd9c9494d4 Add 1 tablespoon of oil to the same skillet and heat over medium high. Add scallion whites and garlic; saute until fragrant, about 1 minute.
92b1be12-5a73-4e14-822c-00cd9c9494d4 Add the bean sprouts to the skillet. Cook until slightly tender but still crisp, about 1 minute. Stir sauce into pan, then remove from heat. Add tofu, spaghetti squash, and cilantro leaves to skillet, stirring to combine.
92b1be12-5a73-4e14-822c-00cd9c9494d4 Stir egg back to skillet. Divide between plates. Garnish with peanuts and scallion greens. Serve with lime wedges to squeeze over before eating.
64d5c604-3f14-4828-907e-9e9bbeb3490a Gather the ingredients. Preheat your waffle iron and lightly grease with butter, oil, or cooking spray. Preheat the oven to 250 F.
64d5c604-3f14-4828-907e-9e9bbeb3490a In a small mixing bowl, combine the almond flour, baking powder, stevia, and salt. Whisk together until mixed. Set aside.
64d5c604-3f14-4828-907e-9e9bbeb3490a Add the egg whites to a medium bowl and beat until doubled in volume and stiff peaks form. Set aside.
64d5c604-3f14-4828-907e-9e9bbeb3490a In a third large mixing bowl, combine the egg yolks, almond butter, melted butter, milk, and vanilla. Add the dry ingredients and mix until combined.
64d5c604-3f14-4828-907e-9e9bbeb3490a Carefully fold in the egg whites, a large dollop at a time, until just combined. Be careful not to over-mix and knock all of the air out of the whipped egg whites.
64d5c604-3f14-4828-907e-9e9bbeb3490a Add 1/4 of the batter to your preheated, greased waffle iron and close the lid. Cook until the waffle is browned on both sides and cooked through. This will take just a few minutes or up to 10 minutes depending on your waffle iron.
64d5c604-3f14-4828-907e-9e9bbeb3490a Place the first waffle on a baking sheet and place in the preheated oven. Repeat with the remaining batter, storing the completed waffles in the oven to keep warm and crisp until all of the batter is used up.
64d5c604-3f14-4828-907e-9e9bbeb3490a Serve warm with toppings of your choice.
870d7fca-9b3c-470b-9bc0-5c702617a238 Gather the ingredients.
870d7fca-9b3c-470b-9bc0-5c702617a238 Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a medium skillet over medium-high. Add the cauliflower, garlic, and 1/4 cup water. Cover, reduce heat to medium, and cook until cauliflower is browned in spots and tender, 5 to 6 minutes.
870d7fca-9b3c-470b-9bc0-5c702617a238 Remove skillet from heat, and let the cauliflower cool, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
870d7fca-9b3c-470b-9bc0-5c702617a238 Add the cooled cauliflower and garlic, remaining 2 tablespoons oil, tahini, lemon juice, paprika, and cumin to the bowl of a food processor. Process, drizzling in 1 tablespoon of water at a time (up to 4 tablespoons), until the hummus is smooth and reaches the desired consistency. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
870d7fca-9b3c-470b-9bc0-5c702617a238 To serve, spread the hummus in a shallow bowl. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with paprika. Serve with cut veggies for dipping.
2f95d66f-60a7-402e-808e-2e19d7466ac3 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 425 F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
2f95d66f-60a7-402e-808e-2e19d7466ac3 Grate the cauliflower on a box grater or in a food processor. You may need to add the cauliflower to the food processor in batches.
2f95d66f-60a7-402e-808e-2e19d7466ac3 Transfer the grated cauliflower to a large bowl. Add the eggs, 1 cup of the mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, oregano, and salt and pepper. Stir the contents until they come together and form a loose dough.
2f95d66f-60a7-402e-808e-2e19d7466ac3 Transfer the dough to the prepared baking sheet. Pat down with moistened hands to form a rectangular crust. It should be about 1/2 an inch thick.
2f95d66f-60a7-402e-808e-2e19d7466ac3 Bake until golden brown and dry to the touch, about 25 minutes.
2f95d66f-60a7-402e-808e-2e19d7466ac3 Melt the butter in a small bowl. Add the minced garlic. Drizzle the garlic butter over the top of the cauliflower crust.
2f95d66f-60a7-402e-808e-2e19d7466ac3 Sprinkle the remaining mozzarella cheese over the top. If you are adding the crushed red pepper flakes, sprinkle the desired amount over the top as well. Bake again until the cheese has melted about 5 to 10 minutes.
2f95d66f-60a7-402e-808e-2e19d7466ac3 Remove from the oven and top with chopped parsley if you wish.
2f95d66f-60a7-402e-808e-2e19d7466ac3 Slice into sticks and serve immediately.
9365127d-1458-44e0-91da-f023d6415df1 Gather the ingredients.
9365127d-1458-44e0-91da-f023d6415df1 Lay the tortilla chips into a pan or plate that is oven-proof and that you want to serve from. Use one larger pan or plate or two medium pans or plates for individual servings. Preheat the oven to 425 F.
9365127d-1458-44e0-91da-f023d6415df1 Add the shredded rotisserie chicken to a microwave-safe bowl. Stir the taco seasoning into the chicken and microwave for 2 minutes or until the chicken is heated through.
9365127d-1458-44e0-91da-f023d6415df1 Top the tortilla chips with the chicken mixture and then the cheddar cheese. Place into the preheated oven and bake for 5 to 7 minutes or until the cheese is melted and the edges of the chips are crisped.
9365127d-1458-44e0-91da-f023d6415df1 While the chips are baking, prepare the queso. Add the diced tomatoes and green chiles and the Velveeta cheese to a medium-sized, microwave-safe bowl. Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes or until the mixture is totally melted. Stir to combine.
9365127d-1458-44e0-91da-f023d6415df1 Drizzle the queso over the top of the baked chips and then top with guacamole, sour cream, salsa, and jalapeno.
6384b361-33f5-4f4b-9f18-1afed8371e9a Gather the ingredients and preheat the oven to 375F.
6384b361-33f5-4f4b-9f18-1afed8371e9a Lay each skin down on a non-stick baking sheet, and spread them out so they take up as much space as possible without overlapping. Sprinkle with onion powder, then lay a sprig of fresh herbs (or an individual leaf of fresh sage) on top of each one, if using.
6384b361-33f5-4f4b-9f18-1afed8371e9a Lay a second non-stick baking sheet on top of the first, tightly sandwiching the skins.
6384b361-33f5-4f4b-9f18-1afed8371e9a Bake for 20 minutes. You should be able to hear sizzling and popping as the skin renders.
6384b361-33f5-4f4b-9f18-1afed8371e9a Remove the pans and let skins cool for several minutes before lifting off the top pan. If you're not using a non-stick pan, allow the skins to sit for 15 minutes after cooking. As they cool, they'll release from the surface naturally (or with minimal help from a spatula).
6384b361-33f5-4f4b-9f18-1afed8371e9a Carefully remove the skins from the sheet they'll be fragile transfer to a paper towel-lined plate, and season with Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper.
6384b361-33f5-4f4b-9f18-1afed8371e9a Keep skins whole for use as chips, crackers, or sandwich filling, or crumble for use as a garnish. Keep any leftovers in a tightly sealed container in a cool, dry place for up to three days.
a2ea9436-8754-4a4f-b508-bd32bedef09d Gather the ingredients.
a2ea9436-8754-4a4f-b508-bd32bedef09d Preheat the oven to 350 F. Melt the mozzarella cheese in a microwave-safe bowl in thirty-second increments, stirring in between until completed melted.
a2ea9436-8754-4a4f-b508-bd32bedef09d With a whisk or fork, quickly mix the dry ingredients into the melted mozzarella. You can whisk together the dry ingredients before adding them to the cheese if you want to make sure they are completed blended. Knead the ingredients with your hands until it forms a soft dough.
a2ea9436-8754-4a4f-b508-bd32bedef09d Since you cant use flour to dust the surface, roll out the dough in between two sheets of parchment paper to prevent sticking. Roll out the dough as thin as you can. The thinner the dough, the thinner the chip. The chips will puff when baked.
a2ea9436-8754-4a4f-b508-bd32bedef09d Cut the dough into triangles using a pizza cutter. You can make them whatever size you like.
a2ea9436-8754-4a4f-b508-bd32bedef09d Place the triangles onto a parchment-lined baking sheet. Make sure they are slightly apart from each other. All of the chips should fit on an average-size baking sheet. Bake for 15 minutes, flipping halfway through until golden brown and crisp on both sides.
a2ea9436-8754-4a4f-b508-bd32bedef09d Allow them to cool slightly and serve with your favorite dips like guacamole, salsa, or queso.
053777f1-dd0b-46fc-91e5-f948f788f870 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F and line 2 rimmed sheet pans with parchment paper.
053777f1-dd0b-46fc-91e5-f948f788f870 Add the almond flour, cocoa powder, salt, and baking soda to a bowl. Whisk until thoroughly combined and set aside.
053777f1-dd0b-46fc-91e5-f948f788f870 Cream the unsalted butter and sweetener using a hand mixer or stand mixer. Beat until lightened in color and fluffy.
053777f1-dd0b-46fc-91e5-f948f788f870 Mix in the eggs and the vanilla extract.
053777f1-dd0b-46fc-91e5-f948f788f870 Stir in the flour mixture, just until incorporated, then fold in the chocolate chips.
053777f1-dd0b-46fc-91e5-f948f788f870 Scoop out approximately 1 1/2-ounce balls and place on 2 prepared sheet pans. Note that these cookies will spread a little, so keep them a couple of inches apart on the baking sheets.
053777f1-dd0b-46fc-91e5-f948f788f870 Flatten the top of each cookie very slightly and sprinkle with a bit of sea salt.
053777f1-dd0b-46fc-91e5-f948f788f870 Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until just set. The cookies will be very soft but will firm up slightly as they cool.
239dd94d-95bd-4627-bc57-baf1a602f1ce Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 400 F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
239dd94d-95bd-4627-bc57-baf1a602f1ce Chop the bacon into a small dice. Add it to a sauté pan and cook on medium heat until they are almost crisp but still have a little fat and arent totally browned.
239dd94d-95bd-4627-bc57-baf1a602f1ce Drain the grease from the bacon on a paper towel-lined plate and set aside.
239dd94d-95bd-4627-bc57-baf1a602f1ce Add the cream cheese, shredded cheddar, green onions, and garlic powder to a medium-sized bowl. Mash the ingredients together until they are combined and all of the ingredients are equally dispersed throughout the cream cheese.
239dd94d-95bd-4627-bc57-baf1a602f1ce Cut each jalapeño in half lengthwise. Scoop out the seeds and ribs with a teaspoon. Make sure to wear plastic gloves when you do this step to avoid getting the peppers' spicy oil on your hands.
239dd94d-95bd-4627-bc57-baf1a602f1ce Stuff each jalapeño half with about a tablespoon of the cream cheese mixture. Do not overstuff as the filling will overflow as it bakes. Place them on the prepared baking sheet.
239dd94d-95bd-4627-bc57-baf1a602f1ce Sprinkle about a teaspoon of the bacon bits onto each popper. Press gently to make sure the bacon sticks and does not fall off.
239dd94d-95bd-4627-bc57-baf1a602f1ce Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until the peppers are softened and the bacon is browned and crisp.
239dd94d-95bd-4627-bc57-baf1a602f1ce Serve immediately.
